178
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:52,080
(Prapai)

179
00:15:10,160 --> 00:15:14,280
What are you looking for?
Do you need any help?

180
00:15:14,680 --> 00:15:16,440
Oh, nothing.

181
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:20,600
Hold on, Pupaa.

182
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:22,920
I want to be straight.

183
00:15:23,120 --> 00:15:25,800
If Pai moves out,

184
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:29,480
can I rent out the room again?

185
00:15:30,240 --> 00:15:31,280
Move out?

186
00:15:33,040 --> 00:15:35,480
You didn’t know?

187
00:15:36,120 --> 00:15:40,240
This morning Pai was asking me
to help find her a new room.

188
00:15:53,800 --> 00:15:56,160
Honey, you’re back.

189
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:59,440
Honey, that’s my friend Pai.

190
00:16:00,800 --> 00:16:03,000
I’m really sorry.

191
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:05,560
Honey,
Pai will be sleeping over tonight.

192
00:16:05,560 --> 00:16:07,760
Why didn’t you call me first?

193
00:16:07,760 --> 00:16:09,960
I was close by already.

194
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:11,540
Cartoon,

195
00:16:11,540 --> 00:16:13,760
I’m sorry I didn’t know
you lived with your boyfriend.

196
00:16:13,760 --> 00:16:15,840
It’s okay. Bo doesn’t mind.

197
00:16:15,840 --> 00:16:17,840
You can sleep on the bed
with me tonight.

198
00:16:17,840 --> 00:16:20,640
No problem. You guys have the bed.
I’ll sleep on the sofa.

199
00:16:20,640 --> 00:16:24,760
It’s alright. You want some water?
Come here.

200
00:16:24,760 --> 00:16:26,800
Feel at home. You’re welcome.

201
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:34,000
Stop it, Bo. What time is this?

202
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:35,200
Bo.

203
00:16:36,880 --> 00:16:37,680
Come on.

204
00:16:37,680 --> 00:16:38,480
Be quiet.

205
00:16:39,160 --> 00:16:40,400
Just a little kiss.

206
00:16:41,360 --> 00:16:43,360
Come on, come on.

207
00:16:44,720 --> 00:16:46,680
I haven’t seen you the entire day.

208
00:16:58,960 --> 00:17:00,480
(Missed call)

209
00:17:02,680 --> 00:17:05,040
(Pupaa 22)

210
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:05,800
(Pupaa)

211
00:17:17,320 --> 00:17:18,880
What’s up, Pupaa?

212
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:20,120
Where are you?

213
00:17:20,600 --> 00:17:21,480
Why aren’t you back yet?

214
00:17:21,840 --> 00:17:23,360
I’m at a friend’s place.

215
00:17:23,920 --> 00:17:25,120
Why didn’t you tell me?

216
00:17:26,080 --> 00:17:26,680
Oh.

217
00:17:27,040 --> 00:17:29,000
Why do I have to tell you everything?

218
00:17:30,120 --> 00:17:32,520
Well...

219
00:17:34,120 --> 00:17:35,600
It’s your turn for chores tomorrow.

220
00:17:36,160 --> 00:17:37,120
Don’t forget.

221
00:17:42,840 --> 00:17:43,560
Oh.

222
00:17:45,720 --> 00:17:47,080
What’s wrong with him?

223
00:17:50,160 --> 00:17:52,120
Stop it, Bo.

224
00:17:52,440 --> 00:17:53,720
Just a little bit.

225
00:17:53,720 --> 00:17:56,160
No, it tickles.

226
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:14,760
Thank you so much
for having me over last night.

227
00:19:14,760 --> 00:19:16,840
Don’t worry. It’s all good.

228
00:19:16,840 --> 00:19:17,920
I’ll have to disturb you again
tonight...

229
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:22,000
Hello.

230
00:19:23,160 --> 00:19:24,000
Are you wearing yesterday’s clothes?

231
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:26,600
You didn’t go home?

232
00:19:28,080 --> 00:19:29,640
Oh my.

233
00:19:30,160 --> 00:19:32,840
Why don’t kids these days
have any responsibility?

234
00:19:33,520 --> 00:19:36,840
Did you apply for the job
because you really wanted to?

235
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:40,200
Because you keep making
the same mistakes.

236
00:19:40,920 --> 00:19:42,560
If this continues,

237
00:19:43,360 --> 00:19:45,400
you’ll never pass probation.

238
00:19:58,680 --> 00:20:01,240
Once you’re done with Pla, come to me.

239
00:20:05,640 --> 00:20:06,320
That’s wild.

240
00:20:06,320 --> 00:20:07,560
Let’s have dinner tonight.

241
00:20:07,560 --> 00:20:09,200
Sure, but it can’t be too late.

242
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:10,280
I’ve got an early meeting tomorrow.

243
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:11,280
Okay, sure.

244
00:20:12,960 --> 00:20:14,080
Where do you want to go?

245
00:20:16,120 --> 00:20:20,120
Oh, Pai, how did it go?
How are your ears?

246
00:20:20,440 --> 00:20:22,440
Pon, this is Pai.

247
00:20:22,440 --> 00:20:25,720
The person I was telling you about.

248
00:20:25,720 --> 00:20:28,240
Pai, this is Pon, the creative director.

249
00:20:28,680 --> 00:20:29,960
- Hello.
- Hello.

250
00:20:29,960 --> 00:20:31,440
Is there a problem with your job?

251
00:20:32,040 --> 00:20:36,320
I couldn’t catch up
with the accounting work.

252
00:20:36,320 --> 00:20:38,360
It’s alright.

253
00:20:38,360 --> 00:20:39,760
Do your main job.

254
00:20:39,760 --> 00:20:42,680
You can finish the job
you’re helping me with tonight.

255
00:20:43,320 --> 00:20:46,400
I was thinking of
letting you do the key visuals.

256
00:20:46,400 --> 00:20:48,000
To put in your portfolio.

257
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:49,760
If this job is really used,

258
00:20:49,760 --> 00:20:52,240
you can say that you did it.

259
00:20:52,520 --> 00:20:53,160
Really?

260
00:20:53,160 --> 00:20:53,880
Um.

261
00:20:54,240 --> 00:20:56,800
Sure. I’ll finish it tonight.

262
00:20:56,800 --> 00:20:57,760
Good job.

263
00:20:58,240 --> 00:20:59,800
Kids these days are so motivated.

264
00:21:01,480 --> 00:21:03,240
I’ll have to excuse myself.

265
00:21:03,240 --> 00:21:04,080
Okay.

266
00:21:04,080 --> 00:21:06,480
- Keep fighting.
- Bye. Thank you.

267
00:21:10,680 --> 00:21:12,960
We’ll buy something back for dinner.

268
00:21:12,960 --> 00:21:14,080
For Bo too.

269
00:21:14,560 --> 00:21:18,160
I’ll go get my clothes too.

270
00:21:18,160 --> 00:21:19,280
- Sure.
- Um.

271
00:21:21,760 --> 00:21:22,600
Prapai.

272
00:21:22,920 --> 00:21:23,840
Let’s go home.

273
00:21:24,760 --> 00:21:27,840
